When creating an issue in the board view, changing the issue type, the board page refreshes. Although the issue type (and the information) is not lost, it would be usefull if the creation of issue in the board works exactly as it works in the backlog view.
h2. Steps to reproduce
 # Access a board,
 # Access the backlog of the board;
 # In the bottom of the backlog issues, use the option "What needs to be done";
 # Change the issue type;
 # the board refresh as a role.

When archieving a version wrong data is send in a webook

*Steps to Reproduce*
# create a version
# click on ... at the right of the version
# choose archive

*Output-Data:*
{code}
{
    "timestamp": 1448029844100,
    "webhookEvent": "jira:version_updated",
    "version": {
        "id": "10004",
        "name": "5",
        "archived": false,
        "released": false,
        "overdue": false,
        "projectId": 10001
    }
}
{code}

*Expected Output*
{code}
{
    "timestamp": 1448029844100,
    "webhookEvent": "jira:version_updated",
    "version": {
        "id": "10004",
        "name": "5",
        "archived": true,
        "released": false,
        "overdue": false,
        "projectId": 10001
    }
}
{code}

When creating an issue via REST API, if you specify a nonexistent project ID, JIRA will return:
{code}{"errorMessages":[],"errors":{"project":"project is required"}}%{code}

It would be great if the error message indicated that the project was not found or invalid instead of stating it was required.

